-- Czech Coal Offers $831 Million for CEZ Plant, Ihned Says
-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 2012-11-21T06:47:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-21/czech-coal-offers-831-million-for-cez-plant-ihned-says.html
Czech Coal AS offered 16.5 billion
koruna ($831 million) for the Pocerady power plant owned by  CEZ
AS (CEZ) , the country’s largest power maker,  Ihned.cz  news website
reported, citing Czech Coal chief executive Lubos Pavlas.  Czech Coal, a mining company that supplies brown coal to
CEZ, didn’t extend its initial bid for the Chvaletice power
station that the utility had also offered to sell, the website,
owned by Hospodarske Noviny newspaper, said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
 placa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  